<TITLE> Two killed by a bus in Chakaria </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Cox's Bazar, June 10 (bdnews24.com)  A passenger bus hit a motorcycle on the Cox's Bazar-Chittagong highway near Chakaria Harbong, killing the two motorcycle passengers at 12:30pm on Thursday. The dead were identified as Abu Sayeed of Chakaria Kakara, 20, and Gias Uddin, 26, of Lohagara in Chittagong. Their bodies were recovered by the highway police of Baniarchora in Chakaria. The officer in charge, Ramij Uddin Sarkar told bdnews24.com that a Shyamoli Paribahan passenger bus traveling from Cox's Bazar to Chittagong and collided head-on with the motorcycle. The motorcycle, which was traveling on the wrong side of the highway, was knocked off the road, resulting in the death of two passengers. The bus fled the scene immediately. A case has been filed at Lohagara police station. bdnews24.com/corr
